04:46.518 --> 04:47.727
[Sighs]

04:49.259 --> 04:50.664
[Grunts]

04:51.229 --> 04:52.693
[Groans]

05:01.244 --> 05:02.481
[Grunts]

05:03.026 --> 05:04.342
[Groans]

05:07.930 --> 05:10.649
[Vomits]

05:24.811 --> 05:27.132
Hey. Sorry I'm late.

05:27.164 --> 05:29.025
Got Lena's nose spray.

05:29.975 --> 05:31.569
You're smoking again, huh?

05:32.984 --> 05:34.184
What?

05:35.211 --> 05:36.766
That security guard died,

05:37.618 --> 05:42.047
and he wasn't just a security guard.
He was a real cop in Long Beach

05:42.080 --> 05:44.115
moonlighting to support his family.

05:44.140 --> 05:45.640
It's been playing nonstop.

05:45.665 --> 05:47.480
I only called like 10 times.

05:47.505 --> 05:48.791
Yeah.

05:51.275 --> 05:54.392
I'm sorry. We were... we were...
we were talking about the next job.

05:54.917 --> 05:57.877
[Sighs] All right, well, I got
to get to work. Lena's napping.

05:57.902 --> 06:00.557
Hey, I can't stay here now. I
got to get home and game this out.

06:01.135 --> 06:02.336
Home?

06:02.361 --> 06:03.571
[Sighs]

06:03.596 --> 06:06.225
You know what I mean.
I can take Lena with.

06:06.250 --> 06:08.650
No. I will get Krystal to take her.

06:08.675 --> 06:10.097
Not Krystal, no.

06:10.640 --> 06:12.724
Smurf will be fine. She
can just, you know...

06:12.749 --> 06:14.863
What, put her in the corner
eating candy while you figure out

06:14.888 --> 06:16.603
what to do about the cop you killed?

06:17.190 --> 06:18.947
- Jesus.
- Cath.

06:20.126 --> 06:21.369
Please?

06:23.385 --> 06:25.428
I got to wake Lena up and go.

06:33.110 --> 06:36.142
[Cellphone rings]

06:38.801 --> 06:40.016
[Sighs]

06:40.041 --> 06:42.353
Yes, Catherine, he left an hour ago.

06:42.378 --> 06:44.106
(Baz) It's me. Turn on channel 2.

06:44.447 --> 06:47.631
- Why?
- Smurf, just turn it on. Now.

07:12.926 --> 07:15.378
If you're just gonna lie
there, I can do this myself.

07:16.348 --> 07:18.372
I'm sorry. It's... it's...

07:18.598 --> 07:19.980
It's throbbin'.

07:21.754 --> 07:24.877
- You used to be worth not surfing.
- Oh, come on.

07:25.137 --> 07:27.742
- It reeks, too.
- Oh, fuck.

07:27.767 --> 07:29.546
You might have to get it drained.

07:32.156 --> 07:33.389
[Sniffs]

07:34.851 --> 07:36.155
Renn...

07:37.046 --> 07:38.639
God, I need a shower.

07:38.664 --> 07:39.870
[Grunts]

07:40.057 --> 07:41.525
You, uh...

07:43.905 --> 07:45.591
You think I could get some more oxy?

07:46.155 --> 07:49.149
[Scoffs] What, are you dealing my
drugs now? Is that what this is?

07:49.174 --> 07:50.594
No. Jesus.

07:53.373 --> 07:55.826
I just sold you 20 yesterday.
Between that and the coke,

07:55.851 --> 07:58.235
you have enough to OD... twice.

07:58.260 --> 08:01.301
I'm big. I got to take more.

08:04.362 --> 08:06.100
- Face the wall.
- What?

08:06.125 --> 08:07.367
Just do it.

08:09.858 --> 08:11.058
Hmm?

08:11.083 --> 08:12.283
[Scoffs]

08:17.051 --> 08:18.519
[Sighs]

08:23.626 --> 08:24.826
Here.

08:27.243 --> 08:28.967
Just leave the cash in there.

08:31.518 --> 08:32.717
Uh...

08:32.743 --> 08:35.001
I'll be flush in a day or two.

08:37.017 --> 08:38.822
- Unh-uh.
- Oh, come on.

08:40.465 --> 08:41.969
You know I'm good for it.

08:44.925 --> 08:47.132
Shit. Fine.

08:49.359 --> 08:51.689
- Don't die on me, okay?
- Mm-hmm.

08:52.119 --> 08:54.156
At least not until you pay me.

09:00.713 --> 09:03.251
[Scrubbing]

09:08.353 --> 09:09.553
[Groans]

09:10.796 --> 09:11.996
[Groans]

09:12.021 --> 09:13.597
I'm sorry.

09:13.622 --> 09:15.862
(Smurf) Oh, that's all right, sweetie.

09:15.950 --> 09:18.905
I raised four boys.
I've seen a lot worse.

09:18.930 --> 09:20.130
[Groans]

09:21.849 --> 09:24.719
Why don't you lay back
down for another sec, J.

09:34.208 --> 09:36.401
Something's happened, J,

09:36.661 --> 09:38.925
something that involves all of us.

09:41.308 --> 09:43.191
You're in this family now.

09:43.216 --> 09:46.245
You're gonna be seeing
things, hearing things

09:46.270 --> 09:49.216
that need to stay in this family.

09:49.516 --> 09:50.825
Do you get it?

09:53.359 --> 09:55.745
Smart kid. Of course you do.

09:57.390 --> 10:00.827
We never set out to hurt anyone.
That's not the way we work.

10:00.859 --> 10:04.558
We don't take stupid
risks, and we're not greedy.

10:05.805 --> 10:07.327
But we're human.

10:07.766 --> 10:10.427
Sometimes one of these
rules get's broken.

10:10.670 --> 10:13.731
Now today we have to deal
with the consequences of that.

10:14.406 --> 10:16.365
Are you gonna be okay?

10:20.687 --> 10:22.032
Good boy.

10:22.993 --> 10:24.721
And if you're not, you just come to me.

10:24.746 --> 10:28.810
There are no secrets in this
family, not from one another.

10:29.798 --> 10:31.886
Especially not from me.

10:34.868 --> 10:37.909
Come on, let's get you
out of these filthy things.

10:39.568 --> 10:42.482
Ugh. Pants next.

10:43.014 --> 10:44.913
You need me to help you stand?

10:49.641 --> 10:51.794
J, I need you to go find Deran.

10:51.819 --> 10:55.081
I got hold of the other boys,
but I think he's probably surfing.

10:55.106 --> 10:56.946
I need you to bring him home.

11:06.140 --> 11:07.470
Underwear?

11:08.858 --> 11:10.423
[Clears throat]

11:39.074 --> 11:41.444
[Groans]

11:44.129 --> 11:45.720
- Oh.
- [Man shouts]

11:45.745 --> 11:47.022
Get in here, man!

11:47.047 --> 11:48.740
Come on, this guy
tried to take my wallet!

11:48.765 --> 11:50.802
[Grunting]

11:50.827 --> 11:52.582
Help me! Come on!

11:57.922 --> 11:59.477
Piece of shit.

12:11.957 --> 12:15.583
Come up from surfing, this
guy's going through my truck,

12:15.608 --> 12:17.444
throws my wallet on the seat.

12:18.671 --> 12:20.592
Like a dipshit, he runs in there.

12:24.399 --> 12:26.101
What are you doing here, man?

12:26.642 --> 12:30.277
Ah, Smurf sent me. She, uh... she
needs you home right away, man.

12:30.309 --> 12:31.878
Oh, yeah? Why's that?

12:31.912 --> 12:33.280
She didn't say.

12:34.482 --> 12:37.335
Hey, throw your bike in the
back. I'll give you a lift.

12:37.850 --> 12:40.263
Nah, man. I like to ride.

12:44.533 --> 12:48.205
♪♪

12:53.833 --> 12:55.335
[Horn honking]

12:56.985 --> 12:58.687
[Honking continues]

13:06.309 --> 13:07.744
Come here, J!

13:08.019 --> 13:09.409
Where you going?

13:37.309 --> 13:38.571
Hey, J!

13:38.596 --> 13:40.798
Sure you don't want a ride, buddy?

13:43.369 --> 13:45.268
Come on, man! Get in the car!

13:48.692 --> 13:51.354
Come on! I'll give you
a ride! Get in the car!

14:07.678 --> 14:09.204
See you back at the house.

14:36.463 --> 14:39.468
- We have to destroy the watches.
- (Craig) What? No!

14:39.493 --> 14:41.343
It's too dangerous to sell them.

14:41.367 --> 14:43.244
They're worth at least 100 grand.

14:43.269 --> 14:46.960
There's not a fence in the world that
won't flip over the death of a cop.

14:46.986 --> 14:49.570
Guy was an idiot, jumping
on the car like that.

14:49.595 --> 14:51.792
You shouldn't have done
the job in the first place.

14:51.824 --> 14:53.258
Oh, that's great. Real
helpful. Thank you, Pope.

14:53.283 --> 14:55.174
Or let Einstein scout

14:55.199 --> 14:57.206
- the security company patrol schedule.
- Oh, eat shit, Pope.

14:57.231 --> 14:58.605
Okay, that's enough.

14:59.588 --> 15:02.384
What about the other guard?
Are you sure he can't ID you?

15:02.409 --> 15:04.803
- I don't think so.
- You don't think so.

15:05.210 --> 15:06.858
No. He can't. It happened too fast,

15:06.883 --> 15:08.917
and he was behind us.
He was blasting away. No.

15:08.942 --> 15:12.150
And the tweakers. You
wore your masks, right?

15:15.048 --> 15:16.896
Yeah. Except when we grabbed them.

15:17.918 --> 15:20.347
Why would they buy drugs
off guys in ski masks?

15:20.372 --> 15:22.254
Because they're shithead tweakers.

15:22.279 --> 15:24.508
Which is exactly why
they wouldn't remember.

15:24.810 --> 15:26.738
You better hope not,
since you let them go.

15:26.763 --> 15:27.982
(Baz) That was the plan, Pope.

15:28.007 --> 15:30.492
The cops match the DNA,
they arrest them, not us.

15:30.517 --> 15:33.210
If they find them dead in the
desert with bullets in their heads...

15:33.235 --> 15:34.907
maybe not the cleanest misdirect.

15:34.932 --> 15:37.954
What about the Range Rover?
You sure no one saw you take it?

15:37.979 --> 15:41.486
(Pope) Yeah. The alley was empty,
plus the street light was out.

15:41.511 --> 15:44.110
Why was J all banged
up when you got home?

15:45.816 --> 15:47.448
You don't believe me?

15:48.362 --> 15:49.567
Ask him.

15:51.011 --> 15:52.211
I...

15:52.769 --> 15:54.955
He stopped short on the way back.

15:54.987 --> 15:57.566
I didn't have my seat belt
on, so my face hit the dash.

15:57.591 --> 15:58.960
He's right. No one saw us.

16:00.065 --> 16:01.327
Okay.

16:01.870 --> 16:04.556
Kilmer's got it in 50 pieces by now.

16:06.547 --> 16:08.820
We... we... we couldn't get to Kilmer's.

16:10.023 --> 16:13.701
W-we... we had to drop it in the salvage
yard, the one we used for the bank.

16:13.865 --> 16:17.434
So, the car with Craig's blood

16:17.459 --> 16:19.819
and a dead cop's bullets in it

16:19.844 --> 16:23.106
is sitting in San Pedro
waiting to be found?

16:23.130 --> 16:26.413
I was worried Craig was gonna bleed out.
I had to make the call. I made the call.

16:26.738 --> 16:29.232
You two are going back to that car.

16:29.257 --> 16:33.508
You're gonna strip it, bleach
it, chop it in 10 pieces,

16:33.533 --> 16:36.072
and then throw it
into the goddamn ocean.

16:36.395 --> 16:38.776
No. No, why... why us?

16:39.035 --> 16:41.085
It was Baz's call. Baz made the call.

16:41.110 --> 16:44.133
He wouldn't have had to if you
hadn't screwed up in the first place.

16:44.297 --> 16:45.499
What about him?

16:45.524 --> 16:47.283
Huh? He's a part of the family now.

16:47.308 --> 16:48.951
W-why is he getting a free ride?

16:49.316 --> 16:52.839
W-why do we always have to do
the grunt work? It's bullshit.

16:55.066 --> 16:59.866
J, after school tomorrow, help
your uncles with the car, okay?

17:00.423 --> 17:01.673
Sure.

17:02.572 --> 17:04.505
You happy now, sweetie?

17:22.003 --> 17:23.204
Hey.

17:28.213 --> 17:30.009
Pope lied to Smurf.

17:33.204 --> 17:36.635
The owner of the Range
Rover tried to stop me,

17:37.671 --> 17:39.911
then Pope beat him up with a flashlight.

17:41.077 --> 17:42.278
You tell Smurf?

17:42.303 --> 17:43.852
- No.
- Good.

17:44.280 --> 17:45.935
Good. You did the right thing.

17:46.885 --> 17:48.881
Always come to me first, okay?

17:50.346 --> 17:51.546
What?

17:52.204 --> 17:54.996
Pope checked his license
to find out where he lived.

17:57.514 --> 17:59.404
Is he gonna do something to him?

18:02.449 --> 18:04.984
What kind of family do
you think we are, man?

18:06.709 --> 18:08.084
I got it from here.

18:16.195 --> 18:17.816
[Grunting]

18:25.620 --> 18:28.094
You said you'd redo this
while I was in prison.

18:28.119 --> 18:30.047
Oh, I figured we'd all be better off

18:30.073 --> 18:32.450
if you had something to
smash when you got out.

18:35.381 --> 18:37.323
Pretty tough on me with Smurf.

18:39.722 --> 18:41.301
Just being honest.

18:41.326 --> 18:42.611
Oh, yeah?

18:42.636 --> 18:43.997
That's funny.

18:49.343 --> 18:51.359
What'd that little shit tell you?

18:52.198 --> 18:54.197
Did he tell you I saved his ass?

18:54.484 --> 18:56.214
The guy was about to kill him.

18:56.239 --> 18:57.905
You should have told Smurf, man.

18:58.367 --> 18:59.952
[Laughs]

19:02.407 --> 19:04.811
She was asking about loose ends.

19:05.164 --> 19:06.931
There are none.

19:07.156 --> 19:10.049
- Meaning what, Pope? What... w-w...
- I took care of it. I scared the guy.

19:10.074 --> 19:11.968
- What does that mean?
- I scared the guy.

19:11.993 --> 19:14.458
He couldn't ID us if we
went up and kissed him.

19:14.599 --> 19:16.322
Well, you still should
have said something.

19:16.347 --> 19:18.450
The only loose end is J.

19:18.850 --> 19:20.360
I told you we couldn't trust him.

19:20.385 --> 19:23.272
He's just a kid, man. What
did you expect him to do?

19:25.154 --> 19:27.151
Ease up on him, and then we'll see.

19:27.898 --> 19:29.235
[Grunts]

19:32.197 --> 19:33.528
[Grunts]

19:42.644 --> 19:44.746
He cornered Craig this morning.

19:44.927 --> 19:47.787
Wanted to know where
you grabbed the tweakers.

19:47.929 --> 19:49.264
Did he tell him?

19:49.609 --> 19:51.389
Craig's not that dumb.

19:51.414 --> 19:52.614
Good.

19:56.643 --> 19:58.112
I don't think he's sleeping.

19:58.597 --> 20:00.941
He never checked into
the motel room we got him.

20:02.208 --> 20:04.584
You mean he's wandering
around the house all night?

20:05.565 --> 20:07.268
Or God knows where.

20:09.975 --> 20:12.369
And what's he saying about J?

20:13.337 --> 20:15.586
He's still convinced we can't trust him.

20:21.643 --> 20:24.727
[Banging]

20:35.310 --> 20:38.199
(Deran) Hey! What are doing up there?

20:38.224 --> 20:40.479
What, are you jerking
off? Can you go any slower?

20:40.504 --> 20:42.284
You try working with one arm.

20:43.035 --> 20:45.408
Yeah, well, at least Smurf
knows we did something right.

20:45.433 --> 20:47.067
If we had taken you to a doctor,

20:47.092 --> 20:49.226
ugh, with all the
heat on this right now,

20:49.251 --> 20:51.034
cops would be all over us.

20:51.128 --> 20:52.671
And you know what?

20:52.705 --> 20:54.674
Look on the bright side.

20:54.707 --> 20:56.856
At least we can be broke now, too.

20:58.655 --> 20:59.990
I'm sick of it, man.

21:00.519 --> 21:01.771
I'm serious.

21:01.796 --> 21:05.219
We do all the hard work,
and she controls the cash?

21:05.244 --> 21:07.913
Nah, man. Nah.

21:07.938 --> 21:10.542
I'm pulling my own
jobs if this keeps up.

21:16.081 --> 21:18.926
You know? You and me, man.

21:19.571 --> 21:20.961
What do you think about that?

21:22.525 --> 21:23.817
Yeah.

21:24.454 --> 21:25.712
I'm in.

21:26.337 --> 21:30.008
You know, I would love to see
Smurf on her knees right now,

21:30.139 --> 21:32.709
getting metal sparks
in her hair and shit.

21:32.982 --> 21:35.189
And Pope and Baz,
where the hell are they?

21:35.775 --> 21:38.057
You know, Pope... fine, I get it.

21:38.082 --> 21:40.585
He'd probably cut off his own
hand to see what it looks like.

21:40.979 --> 21:43.923
But Baz... Oh, shit.

21:43.956 --> 21:46.259
God forbid Baz gets his hands dirty.

21:46.292 --> 21:49.148
No way. Not her favorite, Baz.

21:50.968 --> 21:52.747
What are you doing? You working or what?

21:53.809 --> 21:55.336
I got to piss.

22:09.531 --> 22:10.731
[Grunts]

22:20.058 --> 22:21.960
[Chuckles]

22:57.708 --> 22:59.064
(Pope) Where is it?

23:00.676 --> 23:02.535
The watch I gave you.

23:02.739 --> 23:04.198
You heard Smurf.

23:04.669 --> 23:07.539
I gave it to Nicky. You told me to.

23:09.395 --> 23:10.817
Get it back.

23:15.648 --> 23:17.331
What else are you hiding?

23:20.461 --> 23:22.303
I'm not hiding anything.

23:24.162 --> 23:26.920
That was my go-to when I was your age.

23:28.920 --> 23:31.370
Hid all sorts of shit in there from her.

23:38.280 --> 23:40.105
Well, get dressed.
I'll take you to school.

23:40.408 --> 23:43.218
Um, Nicky's taking me, but thank you.

23:43.243 --> 23:46.813
She called Smurf when you were
showering. I said we'd pick her up.

23:47.670 --> 23:48.907
[Sniffles]

24:13.276 --> 24:14.617
[Metal clangs]

24:32.195 --> 24:35.900
[Gate opens, closes]

24:47.122 --> 24:48.322
[Car door closes]

24:53.336 --> 24:57.006
<i>♪ 'Cause I don't wanna come
back down from this cloud ♪</i>

24:57.031 --> 24:58.398
Whoa, nice!

24:58.423 --> 25:00.179
I blew through a stop
sign the other day.

25:00.204 --> 25:02.765
- My mom almost had a seizure.
- Yeah?

25:02.790 --> 25:05.674
Yeah, she's like the queen
bitch of the fun police.

25:05.699 --> 25:08.890
Even my dad is sick of her,
and he's about as fun as Ebola.

25:08.915 --> 25:11.064
He just made O-5 lieutenant commander,

25:11.089 --> 25:13.190
and I'm like, "Great,
cool. Christmas in Cabo."

25:13.215 --> 25:16.855
And even he was game, but of
course she talked him out of it.

25:17.159 --> 25:19.226
How much do you need for Cabo?

25:20.277 --> 25:21.759
I don't know. Like 2 grand?

25:21.792 --> 25:24.495
So steal it. Rob a bank.

25:27.348 --> 25:28.776
I'm serious.

25:28.801 --> 25:32.856
Get some cash, drive yourself
down to Cabo. You're old enough.

25:32.881 --> 25:34.149
You deserve Cabo.

25:34.174 --> 25:37.087
[Chuckles] My parents
would so come after me.

25:37.112 --> 25:38.748
Not if you tied them up.

25:39.776 --> 25:41.759
You could do it while they're sleeping.

25:42.291 --> 25:43.863
Do your dad first.

25:44.763 --> 25:46.379
[Laughs]

25:46.404 --> 25:49.252
Jesus, J. You didn't tell
me your uncle was psycho.

25:50.029 --> 25:51.961
That's a cool watch.

25:51.986 --> 25:54.022
Thanks. J gave it to me.

25:54.239 --> 25:57.488
Oh, shit. Wow, man.

25:57.513 --> 26:00.380
Yeah, and I'll never take it off.

26:24.370 --> 26:25.574
Catch.

26:25.599 --> 26:26.867
Time for an upgrade.

26:28.382 --> 26:29.918
Can buy my own phone, Smurf.

26:29.943 --> 26:31.773
Why, I can't buy you a gift?

26:32.176 --> 26:34.771
Can't be calling Cath
every time I want you,

26:34.796 --> 26:37.907
not that she knows where
you are half the time anyway.

26:37.932 --> 26:40.082
- Well, thank you, Mother.
- Mm-hmm.

26:41.493 --> 26:44.243
- Pope tossed J's room this morning.
- [Sighs]

26:44.268 --> 26:45.575
Looking for what?

26:45.600 --> 26:47.069
He said J did it,

26:47.111 --> 26:49.847
and he took my truck
and he drove J to school.

26:49.873 --> 26:52.640
I thought trying to stop him
might make it a little bit worse.

26:52.665 --> 26:53.865
Yeah.

26:55.123 --> 26:57.319
You think we can get him
back on those meds again?

26:57.344 --> 27:00.268
You remember what happened
last time we suggested that?

27:00.889 --> 27:03.427
Listen... You know we
don't have to do this.

27:03.452 --> 27:05.551
We are not gonna starve to death.

27:05.576 --> 27:08.399
Sweetie, it's not worth the risk.

27:08.424 --> 27:10.890
Throw the watches in, Barry.

27:10.915 --> 27:12.115
Okay.

27:44.191 --> 27:47.295
(Lena) Is this a good
clown or a bad clown?

27:48.014 --> 27:49.214
Lena?

27:50.979 --> 27:52.967
It looks like a bad clown.

28:09.392 --> 28:11.696
♪♪

28:36.404 --> 28:37.767
What are you doing here?

28:38.388 --> 28:40.031
I brought Lena a present.

28:43.295 --> 28:44.872
You never answered my letter.

28:45.629 --> 28:46.831
Which one?

28:46.856 --> 28:49.271
- I mean, there were a hell of a lot...
- You know which one.

28:51.240 --> 28:52.621
What was I supposed to say?

28:53.349 --> 28:55.338
Maybe you thought I didn't mean it.

28:55.839 --> 28:58.899
You got to go now. Okay? Baz...
He could be here any minute.

28:58.924 --> 29:00.751
I've meant it since we were kids.

29:01.096 --> 29:02.436
Which is why...

29:04.155 --> 29:05.857
Yeah, no. You've...
you've made this bigger

29:05.882 --> 29:07.144
- in your mind.
- Nope.

29:07.405 --> 29:08.918
You liked it, too.

29:08.951 --> 29:12.608
I was angry. Baz and I were
fighting. I was drunk. I...

29:13.323 --> 29:14.691
I had a new baby.

29:14.725 --> 29:16.910
It was no big deal.
At least, not for me.

29:18.497 --> 29:20.182
Have you told Baz?

29:20.787 --> 29:22.725
No, because it was no big deal.

29:23.888 --> 29:25.527
Maybe I should tell him.

29:25.552 --> 29:26.898
Tell Daddy what?

29:28.544 --> 29:31.847
That I love him, sweetheart.

29:31.872 --> 29:36.549
And I-I need people to know
that and be happy for us.

29:39.103 --> 29:40.376
Please.

30:03.181 --> 30:04.381
Baby?

30:04.406 --> 30:05.606
Yes?

30:05.631 --> 30:07.478
Do you remember our secret word?

30:09.673 --> 30:11.693
- Snowflake.
- That's right.

30:12.329 --> 30:13.958
And you remember what to do?

30:14.306 --> 30:17.186
Good. Don't forget it.

30:25.329 --> 30:27.456
So, there's the frequency.

30:27.481 --> 30:29.019
Who can tell me the wavelength?

30:31.567 --> 30:35.709
Okay. Uh, could someone at
least shout out the wrong answer?

30:36.092 --> 30:39.490
And from the ashes of ignorance
we can pluck out a little learning?

30:39.515 --> 30:40.740
Come on, guys.

30:44.356 --> 30:46.726
It's 588 nanometers.

30:48.942 --> 30:51.596
That is not the wrong answer, Josh.

30:52.723 --> 30:55.271
[School bell rings]

30:55.296 --> 30:58.333
Okay. Lab's due Friday. No late labs.

31:05.230 --> 31:06.858
Hey. Hang back a sec.

31:11.371 --> 31:15.484
I, um... I heard about your mom.

31:16.432 --> 31:20.482
I just wanted to check in,
see if you're all right.

31:21.439 --> 31:23.182
- Yeah. I'm fine, thanks.
- Yeah?

31:23.207 --> 31:24.561
Where are you living?

31:25.151 --> 31:27.322
With my grandmother and my uncles.

31:27.666 --> 31:30.968
And is that... feeling okay?

31:31.882 --> 31:33.082
Yeah.

31:33.632 --> 31:34.832
Good.

31:35.234 --> 31:37.274
Good. You're lucky to have family.

31:40.078 --> 31:42.866
You're an excellent student, Josh.

31:43.390 --> 31:45.300
I'd hate to see that change.

31:45.742 --> 31:51.610
If you need any special
help, I'm here for you, okay?

31:52.809 --> 31:54.222
Thank you, Ms. Anderson.

31:54.247 --> 31:56.987
You can call me Alexa outside of class.

31:57.012 --> 31:58.212
If you want.

32:00.333 --> 32:04.492
And you, uh, might want to let Nicky
do her own homework once in a while.

32:04.517 --> 32:05.920
It'd be good for her.

32:06.302 --> 32:09.072
[Chuckles]

32:09.199 --> 32:11.691
- What took so long?
- You got to do your own homework.

32:11.716 --> 32:13.039
- No!
- She knows.

32:34.384 --> 32:37.622
♪♪

32:58.356 --> 32:59.816
[Doorbell ringing]

33:06.653 --> 33:08.996
Oh, Jonah, thank God you're home.

33:09.021 --> 33:10.930
I'm so sorry to bother you, but look...

33:10.955 --> 33:13.157
I just tripped on my front walk.

33:13.373 --> 33:15.904
I know. I'm late for
a meeting in Del Mar,

33:15.929 --> 33:18.431
and like an idiot, I
locked my keys in the house.

33:18.456 --> 33:20.494
My maid's on her way down,
but I was wondering...

33:20.519 --> 33:22.975
Could I use your bathroom just
to clean up just for a minute?

33:23.000 --> 33:24.492
- Do I know...
- Oh.

33:24.517 --> 33:27.610
- I'm sorry. I don't... I don't...
- Jonah, do you not recognize me?

33:27.635 --> 33:30.106
Oh, I'm... I'm Lynne. Lynne Lambert.

33:30.131 --> 33:32.240
I live right next to the Morellis.

33:56.970 --> 33:58.438
(Miriam) Neeny, hurry!

33:58.463 --> 34:01.007
Come on. Hurry. Hurry.

34:07.101 --> 34:08.931
You know why we do all the shit work

34:08.956 --> 34:11.025
and Baz and Smurf do all the planning?

34:11.262 --> 34:13.495
It's 'cause she thinks
we're the dumb ones.

34:13.746 --> 34:14.992
Uh-huh.

34:15.386 --> 34:19.464
And now J, and all of his
science books and shit,

34:20.848 --> 34:22.931
she's gonna think he's a genius, too.

34:25.661 --> 34:27.063
How you doing up there?

34:27.696 --> 34:29.155
What, are you using your teeth?

34:29.344 --> 34:30.632
I don't hear any tools.

34:30.658 --> 34:32.610
[Breathing heavily]

34:32.636 --> 34:34.938
- What's going on with you?
- B-b-bro...

34:35.264 --> 34:36.916
What, are you high?
You haven't done shit.

34:36.940 --> 34:39.029
I think I took too
many painkillers, man.

34:40.715 --> 34:42.196
How bad is it? Let's see.

34:42.221 --> 34:43.556
Whoa, whoa.

34:43.581 --> 34:44.902
Let's see it.

34:45.786 --> 34:49.110
[Winces]

34:49.135 --> 34:52.184
- Ohh.
- It hurts like a bitch.

34:55.270 --> 34:56.797
You need to go down south.

34:56.918 --> 35:00.574
Right, so Smurf can accuse
me of not doing my share?

35:01.005 --> 35:03.335
If you need to go to
Mexico, you got to go.

35:03.669 --> 35:05.850
Already blaming me for getting shot,

35:05.959 --> 35:07.810
you for screwing up the recon.

35:07.835 --> 35:11.298
Whoa, I didn't screw up the recon, okay?
Those guards were never there before.

35:11.659 --> 35:13.427
Let's just get that straight.

35:15.293 --> 35:17.683
Come on, man. Let's
just get this over with.

35:18.155 --> 35:19.457
Nah, screw it.

35:19.878 --> 35:22.833
Even with the both of us working on
this, this is gonna take three days.

35:23.870 --> 35:25.356
Let's just burn it.

35:25.381 --> 35:27.228
[Laughs]

35:27.253 --> 35:30.187
- It's metal.
- Yeah, not reduce it to ash, dumb-ass.

35:30.555 --> 35:32.491
No, fire will wipe it clean.

35:36.020 --> 35:37.337
[Sighs]

35:50.485 --> 35:51.850
[Television playing indistinctly]

35:51.883 --> 35:53.265
[Cat meows]

36:04.924 --> 36:06.230
[Cat meows]

36:10.620 --> 36:11.973
[Coughing]

36:13.828 --> 36:16.437
[Coughing]

36:20.869 --> 36:22.337
[Sniffles]

36:26.818 --> 36:32.558
<i>[Laughter on television]</i>

36:46.713 --> 36:50.150
[Cellphone rings]

36:51.176 --> 36:53.042
You bring the cat food?

36:53.664 --> 36:56.948
[Cellphone continues ringing]

37:05.366 --> 37:08.737
♪♪

37:51.896 --> 37:53.999
Smurf is gonna shit.

37:54.556 --> 37:56.141
Not if we don't tell her.

38:01.226 --> 38:03.623
- Hey.
- Hey.

38:05.850 --> 38:08.610
At least now we'll see how
well you can keep a secret.

38:13.258 --> 38:15.348
Come on, put your bike
in the back. Let's go.

38:16.409 --> 38:17.903
Come on. [Claps]

38:21.884 --> 38:23.321
[Engine starts]

38:31.827 --> 38:33.533
[Pope grunting]

38:43.264 --> 38:44.863
He's worse than ever.

38:45.842 --> 38:49.525
Hey, what happened to that phone I just
gave you? I tried calling you today.

38:49.550 --> 38:51.928
Yeah. I was walking on the
beach. I didn't hear it. Sorry.

38:51.953 --> 38:56.327
Then put it down your pants on
vibrate. When I call, you answer.

38:56.352 --> 38:57.552
Got it.

38:58.072 --> 39:01.302
They put out a reward
now... $25k for information.

39:01.327 --> 39:02.582
They don't have anything.

39:03.618 --> 39:06.155
If they had anything real, they
would have been here by now.

39:07.351 --> 39:11.317
We lie low, don't get
stupid... We're gonna be okay.

39:11.342 --> 39:13.542
Yeah, except burning the
watches and holding off

39:13.567 --> 39:15.766
on other jobs is not gonna play so well.

39:15.791 --> 39:17.882
You have cash you can
give to Deran and Craig?

39:17.907 --> 39:20.144
Craig will only put it up his nose.

39:20.741 --> 39:23.970
I'll make sure his rent is paid
and take care of Deran and Pope.

39:24.772 --> 39:26.788
What about you, baby? How are you set?

39:26.813 --> 39:28.082
I'm okay for a while.

39:28.273 --> 39:29.542
Not too long.

39:29.863 --> 39:32.836
Okay. Everything went according to plan.

39:33.172 --> 39:34.740
Except for these,

39:34.765 --> 39:38.764
but, hey, anything for the team, right?

39:38.935 --> 39:41.652
You know, those are gonna
heal in two or three days.

39:41.677 --> 39:44.647
A murder conviction sometimes
takes a little longer.

39:44.672 --> 39:45.919
Where's J?

39:45.944 --> 39:47.913
Oh, we dropped him at his girlfriend's.

39:49.239 --> 39:51.041
He won't be home for dinner?

39:51.419 --> 39:54.695
Oh, you know what, I forgot to ask, but
maybe it's because I don't give a shit.

39:54.720 --> 39:55.924
And where's Craig?

39:55.949 --> 39:57.774
What am I, a GPS? I don't know.

39:57.799 --> 40:01.314
He's probably snorting himself stupid
because three days after he got shot

40:01.339 --> 40:04.344
his lovely mother made him go out in
the middle of toxic frickin' nowhere

40:04.369 --> 40:05.997
to cut up a car one-handed.

40:15.442 --> 40:18.516
I mean, the kid is spending a lot of
time at his girlfriend's, isn't he?

40:19.348 --> 40:21.552
Okay, now you sound like Pope.

40:22.426 --> 40:24.184
Well, there's a dead cop now.

40:24.209 --> 40:28.370
I had a talk with J. He will be fine.

40:28.796 --> 40:30.400
Are those for Pope?

40:31.737 --> 40:34.316
I thought you said your hookup
at the pharmacy dried up.

40:35.383 --> 40:38.768
Remember Pope's old shrink,
the one he tried to stab?

40:38.793 --> 40:42.870
I borrowed a few of his files and
paid a visit to one of his patients.

40:44.016 --> 40:46.271
Had to improvise a little bit today.

40:46.296 --> 40:49.645
Ah. So you stole them.

40:52.312 --> 40:55.832
We did things, baby, you and me, right?

40:56.148 --> 40:58.631
Things your brothers never had to do.

40:59.192 --> 41:01.923
When I first took you
in, do you remember?

41:02.019 --> 41:05.621
You used to steal food from the kitchen,
and hide it all around the house.

41:05.646 --> 41:07.261
[Both chuckle]

41:07.286 --> 41:11.434
I think it took you about a year to
believe I was gonna feed you regularly.

41:13.283 --> 41:15.509
God, your parents were shits.

41:21.096 --> 41:23.525
I don't know how you survived.

42:00.244 --> 42:02.280
[Sighs]

42:17.934 --> 42:19.797
You locked both the doors.

42:19.822 --> 42:22.459
Uh, shit. I'm sorry.

42:23.798 --> 42:25.945
I would call, but I-I didn't wanna...

42:25.970 --> 42:27.654
you know, and wake up Lena.

42:33.500 --> 42:35.729
You still pissed at me for yesterday?

42:36.777 --> 42:38.006
No. I...

42:38.379 --> 42:40.446
I just spaced out.

42:51.286 --> 42:52.486
Cath.

42:52.511 --> 42:56.525
[Water running]

42:56.550 --> 42:57.809
[Water stops]

42:59.438 --> 43:01.490
That cop's funeral was huge.

43:02.055 --> 43:03.507
Did you see it on TV?

43:03.532 --> 43:04.732
Yeah, I did.

43:06.712 --> 43:08.829
They're gonna need to arrest someone.

43:08.968 --> 43:11.261
Yeah, maybe someone,
but it ain't gonna be us.

43:13.407 --> 43:14.742
Are you sure?

43:14.767 --> 43:17.691
I'm sure. We cleaned it all up.

43:18.587 --> 43:19.787
Hey.

43:21.129 --> 43:22.550
I promise.

43:22.761 --> 43:25.377
We cleaned it all up.

43:30.938 --> 43:33.259
If SWAT breaks down the door
in the middle of the night,

43:33.284 --> 43:35.101
you'll get on the floor
and let them cuff you.

43:35.126 --> 43:37.289
- Cath, come on.
- Promise me.

43:38.079 --> 43:41.443
I don't want Lena to get shot
because her parents are just stupid.

43:43.526 --> 43:45.823
We're not those people, Baz. We're not.

43:46.893 --> 43:48.342
Okay.

43:49.586 --> 43:51.289
I promise.

43:54.732 --> 43:56.295
I promise.

43:59.965 --> 44:02.210
[chuckles] Jesus.

44:02.543 --> 44:04.110
What's this?

44:06.385 --> 44:08.953
She saw it in, um, the supermarket.

44:08.971 --> 44:13.414
What supermarket? It's like something
out of a Mexican horror movie.

44:14.174 --> 44:16.564
How about a giraffe
or something next time?

44:51.637 --> 44:54.895
[Winces]

45:25.041 --> 45:28.086
- [Glass shatters in distance]
- [Grunting]

45:40.348 --> 45:42.459
What the hell are you doing?

45:44.153 --> 45:45.353
[Spits]

46:06.919 --> 46:08.278
<i>Rápido, rápido, rápido!</i>

46:08.870 --> 46:11.909
Go, go, go, go, go! Come on, come on,
come on. Let's go, let's go, let's go.

46:11.934 --> 46:14.719
[Men speaking Spanish]

46:18.946 --> 46:22.616
♪♪

46:29.589 --> 46:31.576
(Man) <i>Ah, ándale, ándale.</i>

46:32.089 --> 46:34.591
Over here. Quick, quick, quick,
quick, quick. Come on, come on.

46:35.050 --> 46:36.626
Yeah, upsy-daisy.

46:36.651 --> 46:38.181
<i>¿él Va a estar bien?</i>

46:38.417 --> 46:40.669
- Go outside. We need to work.
- Okay, what can I do?

46:40.694 --> 46:41.894
Go outside. We got it.

46:42.362 --> 46:44.532
How you doing pal? Lidocaine, Lidocaine.

46:44.557 --> 46:47.541
[Speaking Spanish]

46:47.566 --> 46:49.134
Sí, sí. Ay-yi-yi.

46:49.159 --> 46:51.593
All right, all right. Here we go, buddy.

46:55.041 --> 46:57.564
There we go. Fix you right up.

46:57.589 --> 46:59.884
One... two...

47:08.828 --> 47:10.198
Hey.

47:11.866 --> 47:13.811
It's my idiot brother.

